<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idf6a7b218-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5" identifier="/us/usc/t46/s31307"><num value="31307">§ 31307.</num><heading> State statutes superseded</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">This chapter supersedes any State statute conferring a lien on a vessel to the extent the statute establishes a claim to be enforced by a civil action in rem against the vessel for necessaries.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="idf6a7b219-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5">(<ref href="/us/pl/100/710/tI/s102/c">Pub. L. 100–710, title I, § 102(c)</ref>, <date date="1988-11-23">Nov. 23, 1988</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/102/4741">102 Stat. 4741</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
