<p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">Section 31307 provides for preemption of State laws to the extent a claim for necessaries is enforced by a civil action <i>in rem</i> in admiralty against the vessel.</p>
</note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" role="crossHeading" topic="statutoryNotes" id="idf6a7b21d-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5"><heading class="centered"><b>Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries</b></heading></note>
